    • Method Detail

      • create

        public ManagedObject create(ManagedObject managedObject)
        Stores a ManagedObject in the platform. ID should be empty, will be ignored if present.
        Parameters:
        managedObject - the managedObject to create.
        Returns:
        the ManagedObject stored in the platform with the generated ID.

      • get

        public ManagedObject get(String id)
        Retrieves a ManagedObject identified by ID from the platform.

        Does not set withParents, so no parents will be loaded.

        Parameters:
        id - the identifier of the desired ManagedObject
        Returns:
        the found ManagedObject (or null if not found)

      • get

        public ManagedObject get(String id,
                         boolean withParents)
        Retrieves a ManagedObject identified by ID from the platform.
        Parameters:
        id - the identifier of the desired ManagedObject
        withParents - set true to load with parents (parentDevices, parentAssets)
        Returns:
        the found ManagedObject (or null if not found)

      • delete

      • removeManagedObjectReference

        public void removeManagedObjectReference(ManagedObjectReference managedObjectReference)
        Deletes ManagedObjectReferences.

        This method can be used to any of this reference collections:

        • childAssets
        • childDevices
        • parentAssets
        • parentDevices
        Parameters:
        managedObjectReference - the object to delete
        Since:
        0.2.0
